e, Champagne-Ardenne, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"DE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Adelaïde","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin (via French  <b>Adélaïde</b> ), from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>heid</i> ‘kind, sort’. It was borne in the 10th century by the wife of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adelaïde DE PLEURS was born in 1110, in Pleurs, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France, her father, Hugues DE  PLEURS, was 49 and her mother, Guisemode de Ramerupt, was 32. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Hélie DE LA FERTE GAUCHER. She died in 1171, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1110–1171":"1110–1171","1098–1152":"1098–1152","1100–1145":"1100–1145","1126–1180":"1126–1180","1133–1189":"1133–1189","–1232":"–1232","–Male":"Surnud","1062–1114":"1062–1114","1078–1137":"1078–1137","environ 1114":"umbes 1114","before 1145":"enne 1145","1110":"1110","1098":"1098","Abt 1126